From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: sarun <noreply@sarun>
Date: Fri, 03 Jul 2026 16:52:58 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] dep: per-part double-colon nodes bind $* from their own static pattern

xyz:: %z: %a and xyz:: x%: a% carry different stems; the per-part
split was copying the parent's merged output_pattern into every part,
so $* in part 1 used part 2's pattern. Each part now prefers its own
rule's output pattern. Retires
multi_explicit_output_patterns_double_colon.mk.

Corpus 405/410 fail=0 xfail=5 xpass=0; box corpus PASS.

---
diff --git a/src-rs/dep.rs b/src-rs/dep.rs
index 920df3c..1d22f94 100644
--- a/src-rs/dep.rs
+++ b/src-rs/dep.rs
@@ -1711,7 +1711,10 @@ impl<'a> DepBuilder<'a> {
                         c.cmds = r.cmds.clone();
                         c.has_rule = true;
                         c.dollar_at = Some(output);
-                        c.output_pattern = n.lock().output_pattern;
+                        // Each :: part binds $* from ITS OWN static-pattern
+                        // (xyz:: %z: %a and xyz:: x%: a% have different stems).
+                        c.output_pattern = r.output_patterns.first().copied()
+                            .or_else(|| n.lock().output_pattern);
                         c.rule_vars = rule_vars_snapshot.clone();
                         c.actual_inputs =
                             apply_output_pattern(r, output, &r.inputs);
diff --git a/testcase/multi_explicit_output_patterns_double_colon.mk b/testcase/multi_explicit_output_patterns_double_colon.mk
index c89efb9..4b585c5 100644
--- a/testcase/multi_explicit_output_patterns_double_colon.mk
+++ b/testcase/multi_explicit_output_patterns_double_colon.mk
@@ -1,4 +1,3 @@
-# TODO: Fix
 
 test: xyz
 
